			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok, from what I've read of the previous post, it seems you're trying for either a buy or kill/drop. Can you confirm that your faction was good enough to allow the Shak Dratha Blacksmith to talk freely with you, and that he wouldn't mention any quest at all?<BR>
It's likely that the Xakra shield would be given by quest from the Blacksmith (or perhaps the warlord or barman standing close by).<BR>
I'm not sure about how well the faction holds out here, but I know that you can kill a LOT of Gor Taku before they get ratty, and it only takes a few kills for the Shak Dratha to be merely dubious.<BR>
If there are then any quests you can do for them to raise faction, perhaps this leads on to the Xakra shield.<BR>
Unless it's a drop off the higher lev Shak mobs, a quest in the tunnels would be my bet.I've seen a named Gor Taku there, and several special Shak Dratha (warlord etc), so I'm trying my new character, attempting to balance faction enough to let me wander round at liberty, and see who talks to me.<BR>
If anyone gets to map this place/mobs before me, I'd be interested to hear how it goes. :)<BR>
<BR>

